    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-04-03T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-04-03T13:00:00-05:00" n="516"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d516">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">838.51/3129: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gordon</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Port-au-Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-04-03T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 3, 1936—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 3:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>18. Department’s instruction No. 360 of February 4. Minister for Foreign
                        Affairs<note n="5" xml:id="d516fn5">Yrech Chetelain.</note> this morning
                    under instructions from the President sounded me out on the possibilities of
                    signing the proposed new treaty terminating financial control. He said that with
                    the opposition becoming increasingly active as the day of his second
                    inauguration on May 15th approaches, the President would like to announce this
                    last step in the attainment of total liberation.</p>
                <p>I replied that the President already had very substantial concrete achievements
                    to boast of and that the present moment, especially <pb facs="0700" n="601"
                        xml:id="pg_601"/> when he was seeking a loan on the American market, would
                    be a most unfortunate one to raise the question. Amplifying despatch by air
                    mail.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gordon</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
